29/05/2005
SZEGED, Hungary -- Foreign Minister Ferenc Somogyi, his Romanian counterpart Mihai Razvan Ungureanu and Serbia-Montenegrin counterpart Vuk Draskovic approved a strategic plan Saturday (28 May) to develop a joint Euro-region dubbed Danube-Kares-Maros-Tisa.
The diplomats met for the opening of a new provisional border crossing at the point where the three countries meet.
They discussed potential projects aimed at boosting trans-border co-operation and EU integration processes in the region.
(B92, Tanjug - 28/05/05)
